  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "`BlockchainTests/TransitionTests/bcBerlinToLondon/BerlinToLondonTransition.json` has a block that is supposed to fail with `1559BlockImportImpossible_InitialGasLimitInvalid`, but its gas limit of 6283185 should be instead accepted, according to [EIP-1559](https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-1559#specification), as being well within 1/1024 of `parent_gas_limit=self.parent(block).gas_limit * ELASTICITY_MULTIPLIER=3141592*2=6283184`. A better test, IMHO, would be to say 3141592 instead of 6283185 in `src/BlockchainTestsFiller/TransitionTests/bcBerlinToLondon/BerlinToLondonTransitionFiller.json` for the supposedly invalid block. Parent gas limit of  3141592, not multiplied by `ELASTICITY_MULTIPLIER`, is incorrect for a transition block 5, according to EIP-1559.",
